text: Hey Gura! Massive Doom fan here to answer your question about which Doom is the best to play: If you want to go classic, Doom 64 is the best with atmosphere and spooks (I believe Korone blasted through it in one sitting), and Doom 2016 is the best intro for modern Doom. A few Doom fans might argue, but in my experience those are the ones to go for first. (And if you want to pass on that 2016 is an intro to Eternal to Callie, I'm sure she'll thank you.) Some Doom fans may disagree with my suggestions, but they will agree that all Doom is good Doom. If you fall in love with the series as I have, all of them are worth checking out eventually.

text:
It's always our pleasure to support you, all the girls in EN, and all the girls in Hololive as a whole. And I'm really glad you five have become the precious family you have; I hope you'll have one another to lean on for many more years to come. <3

Also Gura, something I wanna mention about having games you wanna play but don't have permissions for: I obviously don't know exactly how your situation works with Hololive, but from what I know of other members, it's entirely possible you'd be allowed to stream like...AWAY from Hololive, if that makes sense? If you wanna play something on stream badly enough. None of us really know the specifics of whether or not you'd be allowed to, so we can't say. But what I DO know for sure is if that's something you wanted to do, there are plenty of people who would be more than happy to watch you.

Again, might be entirely wrong, and I don't mean to just talk about things I don't really know about. I just wanted to make sure you know that we enjoy your content not just because of a shark, or a cat, or any of the wonderful things about Hololive...but cause you're fun to watch and great to hang out with. You should never have to feel like you wouldn't be loved or appreciated somewhere else, just in case you ever feel like you want to try something else.

(One last thing as a quick aside, for everyone: please please please remember to tell your moms you love and appreciate them, and try to spend whatever time with them you can. All your loved ones, really, but today moms especially. You never know what could happen in life, and it...never really hits you how long you have to live without someone until they're gone.)
